    <!-- ---------- Design notes & usability improvements ---------- -->
    <section class="notes">
      <h4>Deliverables included</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Three low-fidelity wireframes (above) — compare layout choices for visual hierarchy and CTA placement.</li>
        <li>High-fidelity desktop mockup (this page) with accessible typography, clear CTAs, and a focused ordering flow.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 style="margin-top:12px">Usability changes & rationale</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Primary CTA above the fold:</strong> "Order Now" and "Reserve Table" placed in the top-right so returning users can act instantly.</li>
        <li><strong>Visual hierarchy:</strong> Large headline + supporting lede and three feature tiles make purpose clear within 3 seconds.</li>
        <li><strong>Faster conversions:</strong> Right-side order panel in hero reduces click depth to place an order.</li>
        <li><strong>Scannability:</strong> Product cards with short descriptions and ratings help quick decisions; consistent padding and card shapes improve scanning.</li>
        <li><strong>Mobile considerations:</strong> Simplify hero and stack content — provide condensed CTA and quick order button; maintain search & location prominence.</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Sufficient color contrast for text, semantic headings, touch-friendly CTA sizes (>=44px), and descriptive link labels.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 style="margin-top:12px">How to use these files</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>The HTML in this page is a functional high-fidelity static mockup. You can open it in a desktop browser to review layout and copy.</li>
        <li>Wireframes show alternative layout directions — pick one and I can produce pixel-perfect Figma/PNG screens or a responsive prototype next.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

